<br>
Epic:<br>
Melee - 36.62dps<br>
Procs - 31.70dps<br>
Stuns - 4.41dps<br>
Total - 72.73dps<br>
<br>
Now let's look at water, I didn't parse this one but based off Cyricus's tests Melee is approx 35dps, now if it casts a spell every 6 seconds and all of them land for full this is an additional 19.33dps (49*2+20)/6sec.<br>
<br>
Water<br>
Melee - 35.12dps<br>
Spells - 19.33dps<br>
Total - 54.45dps<br>
<br>
Thus on raid mobs with perfect positioning the comparison is<br>
Epic 36.62dps<br>
Water 35.12dps<br>
<br>
On raid mobs if backstab is not possible<br>
Epic 36.62dps<br>
Water 25.25dps<br>
<br>
On exp mobs with perfect positioning the comparision is<br>
Epic 72.73dps<br>
Water 54.45dps<br>
<br>
On exp mobs where backstab is not possible<br>
Epic 72.73dps<br>
Water 44.55dps<br>
<br>
Note: it is more likely that a raid mob will not have backstabs possible than a exp mob because of wall pins on some raid mobs.  However I'd still rough estimate 70% of all raid mobs are backstabable<br>
<br>
I have no problems with this breakdown.  I think it's perfectly fine if non epic level 60s can do equal dmg in raid type situations, everyone wants to feel useful.  And it's plain that in non raid situations the epic is vastly superior, so in my mind there is no cause for concern.<br>
<br>
